{"id":726,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":726,"title":"Joshua","subtitle":"","short_title":"Joshua","uri":"/scriptures/bd/joshua","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/joshua.t1","order":".000.1886"},[".title","Joshua"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/joshua.p1","order":".000.1887"},["i","God is help."],"The name also occurs in the Old Testament under the various forms Jehoshua, Hoshea, Jeshua, and Jesus; son of Nun, and successor of Moses; born in Egypt before the Exodus (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/14.26-31"},"Num. 14:26–31"],"); fought with Amalek (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/17.13-14"},"Ex. 17:13–14"],"); was Moses’ minister (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/24.13"},"24:13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/32.17"},"32:17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/33.11"},"33:11"],"); one of the 12 spies (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/13.8"},"Num. 13:8"],"); appointed Moses’ successor (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/27.18-19"},"27:18–19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/34.17"},"34:17"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/1.38"},"Deut. 1:38"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/3.28"},"3:28"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/31.3,23"},"31:3, 23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/34.9"},"34:9"],"). The book of Joshua (see below) contains the history of his conquest of Palestine. He died at the age of 110 and was buried in his own city, Timnath-Serah. He is the highest type of the devout warrior."]]],"refs":null}
